WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.074
Subtitles downloaded from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:09.552 --> 00:00:12.221
(Gate rumbling. chains rattling)

3
00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:20.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

4
00:00:41.418 --> 00:00:43.544
(Horse snorts)

5
00:00:56.433 --> 00:00:58.392
(Rumbling. chain rattling)

6
00:01:42.979 --> 00:01:44.646
(Wind whistling)

7
00:01:55.992 --> 00:01:58.243
- Easy. boy.
- (Grunts)

8
00:02:59.764 --> 00:03:01.890
(Horse whinnies)

9
00:03:11.234 --> 00:03:13.277
(Man) What do you expect?
They're savages.

10
00:03:13.403 --> 00:03:15.779
One lot steals a goat from another lot.

11
00:03:15.905 --> 00:03:18.240
before you know it
they're ripping each other to pieces.

12
00:03:18.366 --> 00:03:20.826
I've never seen wildlings do a thing like this.

13
00:03:20.952 --> 00:03:23.120
I never seen a thing like this.
not ever in my life.

14
00:03:23.246 --> 00:03:25.414
- (Horse snorts)
- How close did you get?

15
00:03:25.540 --> 00:03:28.959
- Close as any man would.
- We should head back to the Wall.

16
00:03:31.588 --> 00:03:33.046
Do the dead frighten you?

17
00:03:33.172 --> 00:03:35.299
Our orders were to track the wildlings.

18
00:03:35.425 --> 00:03:38.635
We tracked them.
They won't trouble us no more.

19
00:03:38.761 --> 00:03:41.179
You don't think he'll ask us how they died?

20
00:03:43.433 --> 00:03:45.225
Get back on your horse.

21
00:03:46.811 --> 00:03:48.687
(Sighs. mutters)

22
00:03:49.939 --> 00:03:52.441
Whatever did it to them
could do it to us.

23
00:03:52.567 --> 00:03:54.151
They even killed the children.

24
00:03:55.111 --> 00:03:57.112
It's a good thing we're not children.

25
00:03:58.489 --> 00:04:01.283
You want to run away south.
run away.

26
00:04:01.409 --> 00:04:04.328
Of course.
they will behead you as a deserter.

27
00:04:04.454 --> 00:04:06.580
If I don't catch you first.

28
00:04:08.958 --> 00:04:11.251
Get back on your horse.

29
00:04:11.377 --> 00:04:13.712
I won't say it again.

30
00:04:31.356 --> 00:04:33.523
(Shrill animal call)

31
00:04:44.827 --> 00:04:47.329
Your dead men seem
to have moved camp.

32
00:04:48.039 --> 00:04:49.706
They were here.

33
00:04:53.086 --> 00:04:54.753
See where they went.

34
00:05:10.186 --> 00:05:12.854
(Echoing creature cries)

35
00:05:41.259 --> 00:05:43.135
What is it?

36
00:05:44.429 --> 00:05:45.554
It's...

37
00:05:46.639 --> 00:05:48.515
(Cracking. creaking)

38
00:05:50.852 --> 00:05:52.936
(Distant scream)

39
00:05:53.062 --> 00:05:55.230
(Horses neighing)

40
00:05:55.356 --> 00:05:57.065
(Galloping hooves)

41
00:06:25.762 --> 00:06:26.845
(Snarling)

42
00:06:28.723 --> 00:06:30.098
(Chittering)

43
00:06:39.275 --> 00:06:44.905
(Coughing)

44
00:06:45.031 --> 00:06:47.032
(Panting)

45
00:06:47.158 --> 00:06:48.909
(Labored breathing)

46
00:06:49.994 --> 00:06:51.828
(Snarling)

47
00:06:54.290 --> 00:06:55.957
(Gasps)

48
00:07:00.838 --> 00:07:02.464
(Crackling)

49
00:07:10.890 --> 00:07:12.557
(Chittering)

50
00:09:00.082 --> 00:09:02.083
(Galloping hooves)

51
00:09:42.541 --> 00:09:43.959
(Stamps)

52
00:09:48.631 --> 00:09:51.091
Go on. Father's watching.

53
00:09:53.302 --> 00:09:55.011
And your mother.

54
00:10:01.185 --> 00:10:04.521
Fine work. as always.
Well done.

55
00:10:04.647 --> 00:10:06.314
Thank you.

56
00:10:06.440 --> 00:10:10.277
I love the detail that you've managed
to get in these corners.

57
00:10:10.403 --> 00:10:12.195
Quite beautiful.

58
00:10:12.321 --> 00:10:14.197
The stitching...

59
00:10:14.323 --> 00:10:16.533
Oh. no. no. no. This stitch is very...

60
00:10:16.659 --> 00:10:18.118
(Arrows impacting. men laughing)

61
00:10:18.244 --> 00:10:20.203
- It's beautiful.
- Thank you.

62
00:10:27.378 --> 00:10:29.462
(Arrow impacting)

63
00:10:33.217 --> 00:10:35.260
- (Sighs)
- (Laughing)

64
00:10:35.386 --> 00:10:38.138
And which one of you
was a marksman at ten?

65
00:10:39.181 --> 00:10:40.682
Keep practicing. Bran.

66
00:10:42.852 --> 00:10:44.811
Go on.

67
00:10:44.937 --> 00:10:47.605
Don't think too much. Bran.

68
00:10:50.026 --> 00:10:51.192
Relax your bow arm.

69
00:11:01.287 --> 00:11:03.163
(Men laughing)

70
00:11:04.332 --> 00:11:05.832
- Quick. Bran!
- Faster.

71
00:11:07.418 --> 00:11:09.419
Lord Stark!

72
00:11:11.464 --> 00:11:12.505
My lady.

73
00:11:13.549 --> 00:11:15.759
A guardsman just rode in from the hills.

74
00:11:15.885 --> 00:11:18.887
They've captured a deserter
from the Night's Watch.

75
00:11:22.183 --> 00:11:24.309
Get the lads to saddle their horses.

76
00:11:24.435 --> 00:11:26.394
Do you have to?

77
00:11:26.520 --> 00:11:28.605
He swore an oath. Cat.

78
00:11:28.731 --> 00:11:30.732
Law is law. my lady.

79
00:11:31.734 --> 00:11:33.818
Tell Bran he's coming too.

80
00:11:35.738 --> 00:11:37.322
Ned.

81
00:11:37.448 --> 00:11:39.741
Ten is too young
to see such things.

82
00:11:39.867 --> 00:11:41.409
He won't be a boy forever.

83
00:11:43.412 --> 00:11:45.080
And winter is coming.

84
00:12:04.225 --> 00:12:06.434
Good lad. go run back and get the rest.

85
00:12:12.566 --> 00:12:14.150
White walkers.

86
00:12:14.276 --> 00:12:16.986
I saw the white walkers.

87
00:12:17.113 --> 00:12:18.988
White walkers.

88
00:12:19.115 --> 00:12:22.158
The white walkers. I saw them.

89
00:12:22.284 --> 00:12:23.910
(Exhales)

90
00:12:30.960 --> 00:12:32.585
I know I broke my oath.

91
00:12:33.796 --> 00:12:35.296
And I know I'm a deserter.

92
00:12:36.173 --> 00:12:38.842
I should have gone back to the Wall
and warned them. but...

93
00:12:40.010 --> 00:12:42.011
I saw what I saw.

94
00:12:42.138 --> 00:12:43.680
I saw the white walkers.

95
00:12:45.641 --> 00:12:47.475
People need to know.

96
00:12:49.645 --> 00:12:51.479
If you can get word to my family...

97
00:12:51.605 --> 00:12:53.898
tell them I'm no coward.

98
00:12:54.024 --> 00:12:55.984
Tell them I'm sorry.

99
00:13:13.002 --> 00:13:14.669
(Whispers) Forgive me. Lord.

100
00:13:19.049 --> 00:13:21.217
In the name of Robert
of the House Baratheon.

101
00:13:21.343 --> 00:13:23.303
- the first of his name...
- Don't look away.

102
00:13:23.429 --> 00:13:26.264
...King of the Andals and the First Men...
- Father will know if you do.

103
00:13:26.390 --> 00:13:29.726
...Lord of the Seven Kingdoms
and protector of the realm.

104
00:13:29.852 --> 00:13:32.729
I. Eddard of the House Stark.

105
00:13:32.855 --> 00:13:35.398
Lord of Winterfell
and Warden of the North.

106
00:13:35.524 --> 00:13:37.984
sentence you to die.

107
00:13:52.791 --> 00:13:54.459
You did well.

108
00:14:22.655 --> 00:14:24.113
You understand why I did it?

109
00:14:24.240 --> 00:14:26.115
Jon said he was a deserter.

110
00:14:26.242 --> 00:14:28.785
But do you understand
why I had to kill him?

111
00:14:28.911 --> 00:14:30.537
"Our way is the old way"?

112
00:14:32.164 --> 00:14:35.833
The man who passes the sentence
should swing the sword.

113
00:14:36.877 --> 00:14:39.254
Is it true he saw the white walkers?

114
00:14:41.298 --> 00:14:44.259
The white walkers have been gone
for thousands of years.

115
00:14:45.427 --> 00:14:46.928
So he was lying?

116
00:14:51.433 --> 00:14:53.768
A madman sees what he sees.

117
00:15:19.712 --> 00:15:21.629
What is it?

118
00:15:24.008 --> 00:15:25.675
Mountain lion?

119
00:15:27.052 --> 00:15:29.387
There are no mountain lions
in these woods.

120
00:15:56.665 --> 00:15:58.333
(Pup whines)

121
00:16:15.559 --> 00:16:17.352
It's a freak.

122
00:16:18.729 --> 00:16:20.021
It's a direwolf.

123
00:16:29.281 --> 00:16:31.532
Tough old beast.

124
00:16:33.827 --> 00:16:35.912
There are no direwolves
south of the Wall.

125
00:16:36.789 --> 00:16:38.081
Now there are five.

126
00:16:39.708 --> 00:16:41.376
You want to hold it?

127
00:16:42.878 --> 00:16:45.004
(Pup whimpers)

128
00:16:45.923 --> 00:16:47.423
(Bran) Where will they go?

129
00:16:47.549 --> 00:16:49.258
Their mother's dead.

130
00:16:49.385 --> 00:16:50.927
They don't belong down here.

131
00:16:51.053 --> 00:16:54.847
Better a quick death.
They won't last without their mother.

132
00:16:54.973 --> 00:16:56.974
- Right. Give it here.
- No!

133
00:16:57.101 --> 00:16:58.768
- (Whimpers)
- Put away your blade.

134
00:16:58.894 --> 00:17:01.813
- I take orders from your father. not you.
- Please. Father!

135
00:17:01.939 --> 00:17:03.731
I'm sorry. Bran.

136
00:17:03.857 --> 00:17:04.899
Lord Stark?

137
00:17:06.694 --> 00:17:08.194
There are five pups.

138
00:17:09.571 --> 00:17:11.656
One for each of the Stark children.

139
00:17:11.782 --> 00:17:14.283
- (Pup cries)
- The direwolf is the sigil of your house.

140
00:17:15.661 --> 00:17:17.870
They were meant to have them.

141
00:17:23.127 --> 00:17:25.294
You will train them yourselves.

142
00:17:25.421 --> 00:17:27.296
You will feed them yourselves.

143
00:17:27.423 --> 00:17:30.299
And if they die. you will bury them yourselves.

144
00:17:38.934 --> 00:17:40.643
What about you?

145
00:17:41.520 --> 00:17:43.187
I'm not a Stark.

146
00:17:43.313 --> 00:17:45.398
Get on.

147
00:17:52.406 --> 00:17:54.490
(Whimpering)

148
00:17:55.451 --> 00:17:56.909
What is it?

149
00:18:01.123 --> 00:18:04.625
The runt of the litter.
That one's yours. Snow.

150
00:18:13.761 --> 00:18:15.303
(Bells tolling)

151
00:19:04.812 --> 00:19:07.980
As your brother.
I feel it's my duty to warn you...

152
00:19:09.233 --> 00:19:11.234
you worry too much.

153
00:19:11.360 --> 00:19:14.695
- It's starting to show.
- And you never worry about anything.

154
00:19:15.989 --> 00:19:19.909
When we were seven and you jumped off
the cliffs at Casterly Rock.

155
00:19:20.035 --> 00:19:24.413
100-foot drop into the water...
you were never afraid.

156
00:19:24.540 --> 00:19:27.166
There was nothing to be afraid of
until you told Father.

157
00:19:27.292 --> 00:19:30.878
(Mimics) "We're Lannisters.
Lannisters don't act like fools."

158
00:19:33.298 --> 00:19:36.843
- What if Jon Arryn told someone?
- But who would he tell?

159
00:19:38.220 --> 00:19:39.345
My husband.

160
00:19:39.471 --> 00:19:43.224
If he told the king. both our heads would be
skewered on the city gates by now.

161
00:19:44.768 --> 00:19:47.895
Whatever Jon Arryn knew or didn't know.
it died with him.

162
00:19:48.772 --> 00:19:50.606
And Robert will choose
a new Hand of the King.

163
00:19:50.732 --> 00:19:54.318
someone to do his job while he's off
fucking boars and hunting whores.

164
00:19:54.444 --> 00:19:56.112
Or is it the other way around?

165
00:19:57.656 --> 00:19:59.991
And life will go on.

166
00:20:00.117 --> 00:20:02.702
You should be the Hand of the King.

167
00:20:03.579 --> 00:20:05.413
That's an honor I can do without.

168
00:20:05.539 --> 00:20:07.164
Their days are too long.

169
00:20:07.291 --> 00:20:08.958
their lives are too short.

170
00:20:14.506 --> 00:20:16.215
(Thunder rumbles)

171
00:20:21.763 --> 00:20:22.763
(Caws)

172
00:20:37.154 --> 00:20:38.821
(Birds chirping)

173
00:20:48.498 --> 00:20:49.707
All these years.

174
00:20:49.833 --> 00:20:52.960
and I still feel like an outsider
when I come here.

175
00:20:54.796 --> 00:20:56.464
You have five northern children.

176
00:20:57.716 --> 00:21:00.009
You're not an outsider.

177
00:21:00.135 --> 00:21:02.637
I wonder if the old gods agree.

178
00:21:03.889 --> 00:21:05.765
It's your gods with all the rules.

179
00:21:12.522 --> 00:21:14.857
I am so sorry. my love.

180
00:21:15.984 --> 00:21:19.612
- Tell me.
- There was a raven from King's Landing.

181
00:21:21.740 --> 00:21:23.282
Jon Arryn is dead.

182
00:21:23.408 --> 00:21:25.910
A fever took him.

183
00:21:28.830 --> 00:21:30.957
I know he was like a father to you.

184
00:21:34.086 --> 00:21:37.129
- Your sister. the boy?
- They both have their health.

185
00:21:37.255 --> 00:21:39.256
gods be good.

186
00:21:49.518 --> 00:21:50.851
The raven brought more news.

187
00:21:52.980 --> 00:21:55.356
The king rides for Winterfell...

188
00:21:56.400 --> 00:21:59.193
with the queen and all the rest of them.

189
00:22:00.112 --> 00:22:02.446
If he's coming this far north...

190
00:22:04.116 --> 00:22:06.033
there's only one thing he's after.

191
00:22:06.159 --> 00:22:09.537
You can always say no. Ned.

192
00:22:17.879 --> 00:22:21.590
(Catelyn) We'll need plenty of candles
for Lord Tyrion's chamber.

193
00:22:21.717 --> 00:22:25.469
- I'm told he reads all night.
- I'm told he drinks all night.

194
00:22:25.595 --> 00:22:28.764
How much could he possibly drink?
A man of his...

195
00:22:28.890 --> 00:22:30.433
stature?

196
00:22:30.559 --> 00:22:33.436
We've brought up eight barrels of ale
from the cellar.

197
00:22:33.562 --> 00:22:34.770
Perhaps we'll find out.

198
00:22:34.896 --> 00:22:36.731
In any case. candles.

199
00:22:42.863 --> 00:22:45.781
Why is your mother so dead set on us
getting pretty for the king?

200
00:22:45.907 --> 00:22:48.659
It's for the queen. I bet.
I hear she's a sleek bit of mink.

201
00:22:48.785 --> 00:22:50.828
I hear the prince is a right royal prick.

202
00:22:50.954 --> 00:22:54.415
Think of all those southern girls he gets to stab
with his right royal prick.

203
00:22:56.334 --> 00:22:58.461
Go on. Tommy. shear him good.

204
00:22:58.587 --> 00:23:00.880
He's never met a girl he likes better
than his own hair.

205
00:23:01.006 --> 00:23:02.715
(Laughter)

206
00:23:37.876 --> 00:23:40.544
- (Pup yaps)
- Gods. but they grow fast.

207
00:23:43.006 --> 00:23:44.507
Brandon!

208
00:23:44.633 --> 00:23:47.635
I saw the king.
He's got hundreds of people.

209
00:23:47.761 --> 00:23:50.846
How many times have I told you?
No climbing.

210
00:23:50.972 --> 00:23:53.933
But he's coming right now. down our road.

211
00:24:00.941 --> 00:24:03.359
I want you to promise me.

212
00:24:03.485 --> 00:24:05.152
no more climbing.

213
00:24:09.991 --> 00:24:11.158
I promise.

214
00:24:13.328 --> 00:24:16.372
- Do you know what?
- What?

215
00:24:16.498 --> 00:24:18.707
You always look at your feet
before you lie.

216
00:24:18.834 --> 00:24:20.751
(Chuckles)

217
00:24:20.877 --> 00:24:22.628
Run and find your father.

218
00:24:22.754 --> 00:24:24.797
Tell him the king is close.

219
00:25:09.217 --> 00:25:12.595
Where's Arya?
Sansa. where's your sister?

220
00:25:22.898 --> 00:25:25.065
- Hey. hey. hey. hey.
- Oh.

221
00:25:25.192 --> 00:25:27.109
What are you doing with that on?

222
00:25:29.529 --> 00:25:31.614
- Go on.
- (Groans)

223
00:25:32.991 --> 00:25:34.658
(Arya) Move!

224
00:25:52.302 --> 00:25:54.386
(Neighs)

225
00:26:56.825 --> 00:26:58.659
Your Grace.

226
00:27:03.164 --> 00:27:04.832
You've got fat.

227
00:27:11.506 --> 00:27:13.173
(Laughter)

228
00:27:16.928 --> 00:27:18.470
- Cat!
- Your Grace.

229
00:27:22.600 --> 00:27:26.061
Nine years... Why haven't I seen you?
Where the hell have you been?

230
00:27:26.187 --> 00:27:29.732
Guarding the North for you. Your Grace.
Winterfell is yours.

231
00:27:33.653 --> 00:27:36.196
- Where's the Imp?
- Will you shut up?

232
00:27:36.323 --> 00:27:37.823
(Robert) Who have we here?

233
00:27:39.200 --> 00:27:40.534
You must be Robb.

234
00:27:43.496 --> 00:27:45.622
My. you're a pretty one.

235
00:27:47.042 --> 00:27:48.917
Your name is?

236
00:27:49.044 --> 00:27:50.419
Arya.

237
00:27:51.629 --> 00:27:54.214
Oh. show us your muscles.

238
00:27:55.550 --> 00:27:57.843
(Chuckles) You'll be a soldier.

239
00:28:00.722 --> 00:28:03.140
(Arya) That's Jaime Lannister.
the queen's twin brother.

240
00:28:03.266 --> 00:28:05.392
(Sansa) Would you please shut up?

241
00:28:14.944 --> 00:28:18.822
My queen.

242
00:28:18.948 --> 00:28:20.949
Take me to your crypt.
I want to pay my respects.

243
00:28:21.076 --> 00:28:22.910
We've been riding for a month. my love.

244
00:28:23.411 --> 00:28:25.037
Surely the dead can wait.

245
00:28:25.163 --> 00:28:27.039
Ned.

246
00:28:36.716 --> 00:28:37.925
Where's the Imp?

247
00:28:41.429 --> 00:28:43.430
(Queen) Where is our brother?

248
00:28:43.556 --> 00:28:45.307
Go and find the little beast.

249
00:28:47.685 --> 00:28:49.353
Tell me about Jon Arryn.

250
00:28:50.605 --> 00:28:52.815
One minute he was fine and then...

251
00:28:54.025 --> 00:28:56.777
burned right through him.
whatever it was.

252
00:28:57.946 --> 00:28:59.947
I loved that man.

253
00:29:00.073 --> 00:29:01.407
We both did.

254
00:29:01.533 --> 00:29:05.869
(Robert) He never had to teach you much.
but me? You remember me at 16?

255
00:29:05.995 --> 00:29:07.830
- (Chuckles)
- All I wanted to do

256
00:29:07.956 --> 00:29:10.582
was crack skulls and fuck girls.

257
00:29:10.708 --> 00:29:13.836
- He showed me what was what.
- Aye.

258
00:29:13.962 --> 00:29:16.588
Don't look at me like that.
It's not his fault I didn't listen.

259
00:29:16.714 --> 00:29:18.549
(Both laugh)

260
00:29:19.300 --> 00:29:21.009
(Sighs)

261
00:29:21.136 --> 00:29:23.178
I need you. Ned.

262
00:29:23.304 --> 00:29:26.974
down at King's Landing. not up here
where you're no damn use to anybody.

263
00:29:28.852 --> 00:29:30.644
Lord Eddard Stark...

264
00:29:31.604 --> 00:29:34.064
I would name you the Hand of the King.

265
00:29:38.528 --> 00:29:40.654
I'm not worthy of the honor.

266
00:29:40.780 --> 00:29:42.197
I'm not trying to honor you.

267
00:29:42.323 --> 00:29:44.032
I'm trying to get you to run my kingdom

268
00:29:44.159 --> 00:29:47.870
while I eat. drink and whore my way
to an early grave.

269
00:29:47.996 --> 00:29:49.830
Damn it. Ned. stand up.

270
00:29:51.374 --> 00:29:53.333
You helped me win the Iron Throne.

271
00:29:53.460 --> 00:29:56.170
now help me keep the damn thing.

272
00:29:56.296 --> 00:29:58.672
We were meant to rule together.

273
00:29:58.798 --> 00:30:02.634
If your sister had lived.
we'd have been bound by blood.

274
00:30:03.595 --> 00:30:05.179
Well. it's not too late.

275
00:30:06.848 --> 00:30:08.515
I have a son.
you have a daughter.

276
00:30:10.351 --> 00:30:12.019
We'll join our houses.

277
00:30:16.357 --> 00:30:18.025
(Woman moaning)

278
00:30:29.871 --> 00:30:31.038
(Sighs)

279
00:30:36.169 --> 00:30:37.085
(Cup falls)

280
00:30:37.212 --> 00:30:40.172
It is true what they say
about the northern girls.

281
00:30:40.298 --> 00:30:41.381
(Giggles)

282
00:30:48.389 --> 00:30:50.724
Did you hear the king's in Winterfell?

283
00:30:50.850 --> 00:30:52.476
I did hear something about that.

284
00:30:52.602 --> 00:30:54.770
And the queen and her twin brother.

285
00:30:54.896 --> 00:30:57.940
They say that he is the most handsome man
in the Seven Kingdoms.

286
00:30:58.066 --> 00:30:59.942
And the other brother?

287
00:31:00.068 --> 00:31:03.278
- The queen has two brothers?
- There's the pretty one...

288
00:31:04.489 --> 00:31:06.198
and there's the clever one.

289
00:31:07.492 --> 00:31:08.992
Mmm...

290
00:31:09.118 --> 00:31:11.370
I hear they call him the Imp.

291
00:31:11.496 --> 00:31:13.288
I hear he hates that nickname.

292
00:31:13.414 --> 00:31:16.792
Oh? I hear he's more than earned it.

293
00:31:16.918 --> 00:31:19.169
I hear he's a drunken little lecher.

294
00:31:19.295 --> 00:31:21.755
prone to all manner of perversions.

295
00:31:21.881 --> 00:31:23.674
Clever girl.

296
00:31:25.426 --> 00:31:27.261
We've been expecting you. Lord Tyrion.

297
00:31:28.596 --> 00:31:30.180
Have you?

298
00:31:30.306 --> 00:31:31.682
- Already?
- Oh!

299
00:31:34.602 --> 00:31:37.312
- The gods gave me one blessing.
- (Laughs)

300
00:31:37.438 --> 00:31:38.480
(Door opens)

301
00:31:42.193 --> 00:31:44.695
- Don't get up.
- My lord.

302
00:31:44.821 --> 00:31:48.490
Should I explain to you the meaning of
a closed door in a whorehouse. brother?

303
00:31:48.616 --> 00:31:50.659
You have much to teach me. no doubt.

304
00:31:50.785 --> 00:31:53.954
but our sister craves your attention.

305
00:31:54.664 --> 00:31:56.665
She has odd cravings. our sister.

306
00:31:56.791 --> 00:31:58.834
A family trait.

307
00:31:58.960 --> 00:32:01.420
Now. the Starks are feasting us at sundown.

308
00:32:02.422 --> 00:32:06.383
- Don't leave me alone with these people.
- I'm sorry. I've begun the feast a bit early.

309
00:32:06.509 --> 00:32:09.845
And this is the first of many courses.

310
00:32:09.971 --> 00:32:12.180
I thought you might say that.

311
00:32:12.307 --> 00:32:14.933
But since we're short on time...

312
00:32:15.059 --> 00:32:16.351
Come on. girls.

313
00:32:16.477 --> 00:32:19.104
(Giggling)

314
00:32:22.317 --> 00:32:24.109
See you at sundown.

315
00:32:24.235 --> 00:32:26.320
(Tyrion) Close the door!

316
00:32:38.750 --> 00:32:41.501
Did you have to bury her
in a place like this?

317
00:32:43.379 --> 00:32:45.589
She should be on a hill somewhere

318
00:32:45.715 --> 00:32:48.050
with the sun and the clouds above her.

319
00:32:48.176 --> 00:32:50.218
She was my sister.

320
00:32:50.345 --> 00:32:52.012
This is where she belongs.

321
00:32:53.181 --> 00:32:55.515
She belonged with me.

322
00:33:00.980 --> 00:33:04.191
In my dreams.
I kill him every night.

323
00:33:05.735 --> 00:33:10.030
It's done. Your Grace.
The Targaryens are gone.

324
00:33:13.242 --> 00:33:15.160
Not all of them.

325
00:33:16.788 --> 00:33:18.580
(Gull crying)

326
00:33:26.089 --> 00:33:28.048
(Man) Daenerys!

327
00:33:31.219 --> 00:33:32.928
Daenerys.

328
00:33:33.054 --> 00:33:35.055
There's our bride-to-be.

329
00:33:36.057 --> 00:33:38.642
Look. a gift from Illyrio.

330
00:33:40.228 --> 00:33:41.812
Touch it.

331
00:33:41.938 --> 00:33:44.147
Go on. feel the fabric.

332
00:33:49.070 --> 00:33:50.070
Mmm.

333
00:33:52.240 --> 00:33:54.074
Isn't he a gracious host?

334
00:33:57.453 --> 00:34:01.123
We've been his guests for over a year
and he's never asked us for anything.

335
00:34:01.249 --> 00:34:03.125
Illyrio's no fool.

336
00:34:03.251 --> 00:34:05.043
He knows I won't forget my friends

337
00:34:05.169 --> 00:34:07.421
when I come into my throne.

338
00:34:11.759 --> 00:34:13.510
You still slouch.

339
00:34:17.890 --> 00:34:20.183
Let them see.

340
00:34:22.979 --> 00:34:25.731
You have a woman's body now.

341
00:34:28.693 --> 00:34:30.402
(Sighs)

342
00:34:43.624 --> 00:34:45.625
I need you to be perfect today.

343
00:34:48.171 --> 00:34:49.546
Can you do that for me?

344
00:34:53.092 --> 00:34:55.677
You don't want to wake the dragon. do you?

345
00:34:57.638 --> 00:34:58.680
No.

346
00:35:05.813 --> 00:35:08.398
When they write the history
of my reign. sweet sister.

347
00:35:08.524 --> 00:35:10.484
they will say it began today.

348
00:35:34.217 --> 00:35:35.884
It's too hot. my lady.

349
00:35:46.979 --> 00:35:48.647
(Gulls crying)

350
00:35:57.156 --> 00:35:59.074
Where is he?

351
00:35:59.200 --> 00:36:02.077
The Dothraki are not known
for their punctuality.

352
00:36:15.383 --> 00:36:19.427
(Illyrio speaks Dothraki)

353
00:36:19.554 --> 00:36:21.471
May I present my honored guests?

354
00:36:21.597 --> 00:36:25.141
Viserys of House Targaryen.

355
00:36:25.268 --> 00:36:26.768
the third of his name.

356
00:36:26.894 --> 00:36:30.272
the rightful King of the Andals
and the First Men.

357
00:36:30.398 --> 00:36:31.690
and his sister.

358
00:36:31.816 --> 00:36:34.693
Daenerys of House Targaryen.

359
00:36:35.778 --> 00:36:37.612
(Speaks Dothraki)

360
00:36:37.738 --> 00:36:40.156
Do you see how long his hair is?

361
00:36:40.283 --> 00:36:43.076
When Dothraki are defeated in combat

362
00:36:43.202 --> 00:36:46.788
they cut off their braid
so the whole world can see their shame.

363
00:36:46.914 --> 00:36:50.750
Khal Drogo has never been defeated.

364
00:36:52.211 --> 00:36:56.089
He's a savage. of course.
but he's one of the finest killers alive.

365
00:36:57.466 --> 00:36:59.593
And you will be his queen.

366
00:37:00.386 --> 00:37:02.262
Come forward. my dear.

367
00:37:42.386 --> 00:37:43.511
Where is he going?

368
00:37:43.638 --> 00:37:46.348
- The ceremony is over.
- But he... But he didn't say anything.

369
00:37:46.474 --> 00:37:47.599
Did he like her?

370
00:37:47.725 --> 00:37:51.478
Trust me. Your Grace.
if he didn't like her. we'd know.

371
00:37:54.607 --> 00:37:56.858
(Illyrio) It won't be long now.

372
00:37:56.984 --> 00:38:00.612
Soon you will cross the narrow sea
and take back your father's throne.

373
00:38:01.864 --> 00:38:05.700
The people drink secret toasts
to your health.

374
00:38:05.826 --> 00:38:08.286
They cry out for their true king.

375
00:38:11.832 --> 00:38:13.708
When will they be married?

376
00:38:13.834 --> 00:38:17.379
Soon.
The Dothraki never stay still for long.

377
00:38:17.505 --> 00:38:19.756
Is it true they lie with their horses?

378
00:38:20.508 --> 00:38:22.801
I wouldn't ask Khal Drogo.

379
00:38:22.927 --> 00:38:25.053
Do you take me for a fool?

380
00:38:25.179 --> 00:38:26.888
I take you for a king.

381
00:38:27.014 --> 00:38:30.141
Kings lack the caution
of common men.

382
00:38:30.267 --> 00:38:31.977
My apologies if I've given offense.

383
00:38:32.103 --> 00:38:34.688
I know how to play a man like Drogo.

384
00:38:34.814 --> 00:38:37.607
I give him a queen
and he gives me an army.

385
00:38:38.526 --> 00:38:40.568
I don't want to be his queen.

386
00:38:45.658 --> 00:38:47.033
I want to go home.

387
00:38:47.702 --> 00:38:49.035
So do I.

388
00:38:50.204 --> 00:38:52.497
I want us both to go home.

389
00:38:52.623 --> 00:38:54.833
but they took it from us.

390
00:38:54.959 --> 00:38:56.751
So tell me. sweet sister.

391
00:38:56.877 --> 00:38:58.545
how do we go home?

392
00:39:01.257 --> 00:39:02.424
I don't know.

393
00:39:02.550 --> 00:39:04.801
We go home with an army.

394
00:39:06.887 --> 00:39:09.180
With Khal Drogo's army.

395
00:39:10.391 --> 00:39:13.393
I would let his whole tribe fuck you.

396
00:39:13.519 --> 00:39:16.604
all 40.000 men and their horses too.

397
00:39:16.731 --> 00:39:18.398
if that's what it took.

398
00:39:25.740 --> 00:39:27.198
(Kisses)

399
00:39:35.708 --> 00:39:38.209
Do you think Joffrey will like me?

400
00:39:38.335 --> 00:39:40.545
What if he thinks I'm ugly?

401
00:39:40.671 --> 00:39:44.090
Then he is the stupidest prince that ever lived.

402
00:39:46.761 --> 00:39:48.094
He's so handsome.

403
00:39:49.263 --> 00:39:51.973
When would we be married?
Soon? Or do we have to wait?

404
00:39:52.099 --> 00:39:55.185
Hush now.
Your father hasn't even said yes.

405
00:39:55.311 --> 00:39:56.978
Why would he say no?

406
00:39:57.104 --> 00:40:00.023
He'd be the second most powerful man
in the kingdoms.

407
00:40:00.149 --> 00:40:02.192
He'd have to leave home.

408
00:40:03.486 --> 00:40:05.862
He'd have to leave me.

409
00:40:06.864 --> 00:40:08.990
And so would you.

410
00:40:09.116 --> 00:40:11.451
You left your home to come here.

411
00:40:11.577 --> 00:40:13.328
And I'd be queen someday.

412
00:40:15.289 --> 00:40:16.831
Please make Father say yes!

413
00:40:16.957 --> 00:40:18.750
- Sansa...
- Please. please!

414
00:40:18.876 --> 00:40:21.753
It's the only thing I ever wanted.

415
00:40:25.800 --> 00:40:27.884
(Music playing. people chattering)

416
00:40:32.181 --> 00:40:33.973
(Laughter)

417
00:40:35.643 --> 00:40:37.811
Fill that up!
Boys. Rodrik. come on.

418
00:40:37.937 --> 00:40:39.979
Come on!

419
00:40:40.106 --> 00:40:42.857
Come here. you little beauty!

420
00:40:42.983 --> 00:40:44.651
(Robert laughing)

421
00:40:58.666 --> 00:40:59.958
Is he dead yet?

422
00:41:05.422 --> 00:41:06.506
Uncle Benjen.

423
00:41:07.716 --> 00:41:09.384
(Laughs)

424
00:41:09.510 --> 00:41:10.718
You got bigger.

425
00:41:12.096 --> 00:41:13.680
Rode all day.

426
00:41:13.806 --> 00:41:16.391
Didn't want to leave you alone
with the Lannisters.

427
00:41:16.517 --> 00:41:17.851
Why aren't you at the feast?

428
00:41:17.977 --> 00:41:20.728
Lady Stark thought it might
insult the royal family

429
00:41:20.855 --> 00:41:22.772
to seat a bastard in their midst.

430
00:41:23.607 --> 00:41:25.984
Well. you're always
welcome on the Wall.

431
00:41:26.110 --> 00:41:28.069
No bastard was ever
refused a seat there.

432
00:41:28.195 --> 00:41:29.904
So take me with you
when you go back.

433
00:41:30.030 --> 00:41:32.907
- Jon...
- Father will let me if you ask him.

434
00:41:33.033 --> 00:41:34.826
I know he will.

435
00:41:37.538 --> 00:41:39.622
The Wall isn't going anywhere.

436
00:41:39.748 --> 00:41:42.417
I'm ready to swear your oath.

437
00:41:42.543 --> 00:41:45.670
You don't understand
what you'd be giving up.

438
00:41:45.796 --> 00:41:47.714
We have no families.

439
00:41:47.840 --> 00:41:51.551
- None of us will ever father sons.
- I don't care about that.

440
00:41:51.677 --> 00:41:54.637
You might. if you knew what it meant.

441
00:41:58.017 --> 00:42:00.476
(Sighs) I'd better get inside.

442
00:42:00.603 --> 00:42:02.896
rescue your father from his guests.

443
00:42:05.941 --> 00:42:07.984
We'll talk later.

444
00:42:16.410 --> 00:42:18.745
(Tyrion) Your uncle's in the Night's Watch.

445
00:42:21.707 --> 00:42:24.042
What are you doing back there?

446
00:42:24.168 --> 00:42:26.377
Preparing for a night with your family.

447
00:42:31.592 --> 00:42:33.509
I've always wanted to see the Wall.

448
00:42:33.636 --> 00:42:35.428
You're Tyrion Lannister.

449
00:42:35.554 --> 00:42:37.096
the queen's brother?

450
00:42:37.223 --> 00:42:38.890
My greatest accomplishment.

451
00:42:40.434 --> 00:42:43.102
And you. you're Ned Stark's bastard.
aren't you?

452
00:42:46.565 --> 00:42:48.733
Did I offend you? Sorry.

453
00:42:50.861 --> 00:42:53.321
You are the bastard. though.

454
00:42:54.615 --> 00:42:56.950
Lord Eddard Stark is my father.

455
00:42:58.202 --> 00:43:00.828
And Lady Stark is not your mother.

456
00:43:00.955 --> 00:43:03.957
making you... the bastard.

457
00:43:05.459 --> 00:43:08.086
Let me give you some advice. bastard.

458
00:43:09.255 --> 00:43:11.047
Never forget what you are.

459
00:43:11.173 --> 00:43:13.508
The rest of the world will not.

460
00:43:13.634 --> 00:43:15.218
Wear it like armor...

461
00:43:16.011 --> 00:43:18.304
and it can never be used to hurt you.

462
00:43:19.974 --> 00:43:22.642
What the hell do you know
about being a bastard?

463
00:43:25.104 --> 00:43:27.563
All dwarves are bastards
in their father's eyes.

464
00:43:43.205 --> 00:43:44.747
(Music playing. chattering)

465
00:43:44.873 --> 00:43:46.457
(Laughter)

466
00:43:49.253 --> 00:43:50.878
You at a feast...

467
00:43:51.839 --> 00:43:53.506
it's like a bear in a trap.

468
00:43:55.509 --> 00:43:57.093
The boy I beheaded...

469
00:43:58.429 --> 00:44:01.347
- did you know him?
- Of course I did. Just a lad.

470
00:44:02.516 --> 00:44:04.600
But he was tough. Ned.

471
00:44:04.727 --> 00:44:05.977
a true ranger.

472
00:44:06.103 --> 00:44:07.603
(Scoffs)

473
00:44:07.730 --> 00:44:09.480
He was talking madness.

474
00:44:10.691 --> 00:44:12.442
Said the walkers slaughtered his friends.

475
00:44:12.568 --> 00:44:14.861
The two he was with are still missing.

476
00:44:16.530 --> 00:44:19.991
Hmph. A wildling ambush.

477
00:44:20.993 --> 00:44:22.076
Maybe.

478
00:44:23.370 --> 00:44:25.913
Direwolves south of the Wall.

479
00:44:26.040 --> 00:44:28.249
talk of the walkers.

480
00:44:28.375 --> 00:44:30.918
and my brother might be
the next Hand of the King.

481
00:44:32.129 --> 00:44:37.383
Winter is coming.

482
00:44:37.509 --> 00:44:38.926
(They chuckle)

483
00:44:39.053 --> 00:44:41.888
- Uncle Benjen.
- Robb boy.

484
00:44:42.014 --> 00:44:43.473
- How are you?
- I'm good.

485
00:44:43.599 --> 00:44:45.850
(Laughter)

486
00:44:46.935 --> 00:44:49.687
Is this your first time
in the North. Your Grace?

487
00:44:49.813 --> 00:44:52.565
Yes. Lovely country.

488
00:44:56.362 --> 00:44:59.697
I'm sure it's very grim
after King's Landing.

489
00:45:00.991 --> 00:45:05.370
I remember how scared I was when
Ned brought me up here for the first time.

490
00:45:07.581 --> 00:45:09.165
Hello. little dove.

491
00:45:10.167 --> 00:45:12.335
But you are a beauty.

492
00:45:12.461 --> 00:45:14.754
- How old are you?
- Thirteen. Your Grace.

493
00:45:14.880 --> 00:45:17.465
You're tall. Still growing?

494
00:45:17.591 --> 00:45:19.425
I think so. Your Grace.

495
00:45:19.551 --> 00:45:21.677
And have you bled yet?

496
00:45:26.809 --> 00:45:28.267
No. Your Grace.

497
00:45:29.770 --> 00:45:31.396
Your dress. did you make it?

498
00:45:33.190 --> 00:45:36.442
Such talent.
You must make something for me.

499
00:45:38.362 --> 00:45:41.406
I hear we might share
a grandchild someday.

500
00:45:42.449 --> 00:45:43.616
I hear the same.

501
00:45:43.742 --> 00:45:45.952
Your daughter will do well in the capital.

502
00:45:46.078 --> 00:45:49.414
Such a beauty shouldn't stay
hidden up here forever.

503
00:46:06.432 --> 00:46:09.058
- Your pardon.
- I hear we might be neighbors soon.

504
00:46:09.184 --> 00:46:12.645
- I hope it's true.
- Yes. the king has honored me with his offer.

505
00:46:12.771 --> 00:46:15.982
I'm sure we'll have a tournament to celebrate
your new title. if you accept.

506
00:46:16.108 --> 00:46:18.192
It would be good
to have you on the field.

507
00:46:18.318 --> 00:46:20.695
The competition has become a bit stale.

508
00:46:20.821 --> 00:46:23.072
- I don't fight in tournaments.
- No?

509
00:46:23.198 --> 00:46:24.740
Getting a little old for it?

510
00:46:24.867 --> 00:46:26.576
(Chuckles)

511
00:46:26.702 --> 00:46:28.744
I don't fight in tournaments

512
00:46:28.871 --> 00:46:31.247
because when I fight a man for real.

513
00:46:31.373 --> 00:46:33.124
I don't want him to know what I can do.

514
00:46:35.419 --> 00:46:36.794
Well said.

515
00:46:38.172 --> 00:46:39.505
- (Laughing)
- Arya!

516
00:46:41.842 --> 00:46:43.551
It's not funny!

517
00:46:43.677 --> 00:46:46.304
She always does this.

518
00:46:46.430 --> 00:46:48.848
This was my favorite dress
and she ruined it.

519
00:46:48.974 --> 00:46:51.434
She always does it
and it's not funny!

520
00:46:51.560 --> 00:46:53.394
(Robb) Time for bed.

521
00:46:54.897 --> 00:46:56.481
(Arya groans)

522
00:47:04.490 --> 00:47:06.157
(Ned) I'm a Northman.

523
00:47:07.868 --> 00:47:12.371
I belong here with you. not down south
in that rats' nest they call a capital.

524
00:47:13.415 --> 00:47:16.167
I won't let him take you.

525
00:47:17.711 --> 00:47:20.296
The king takes what he wants.

526
00:47:20.422 --> 00:47:22.715
(Snorts) That's why he's king.

527
00:47:23.759 --> 00:47:27.428
I'll say. "Listen. fat man."

528
00:47:27.554 --> 00:47:28.596
(He laughs)

529
00:47:28.722 --> 00:47:31.849
"You are not taking
my husband anywhere.

530
00:47:31.975 --> 00:47:33.893
"He belongs to me now."

531
00:47:37.648 --> 00:47:39.690
How did he get so fat?

532
00:47:39.816 --> 00:47:44.111
He only stops eating
when it's time for a drink. (Chuckles)

533
00:47:44.238 --> 00:47:45.613
(Knocking)

534
00:47:45.739 --> 00:47:48.157
(Man) It's Maester Luwin. my lord.

535
00:47:49.618 --> 00:47:51.536
Send him in.

536
00:47:53.830 --> 00:47:56.165
Pardon. my lord. my lady.

537
00:47:56.291 --> 00:47:58.793
A rider in the night...

538
00:47:58.919 --> 00:48:01.087
from your sister.

539
00:48:08.804 --> 00:48:11.430
- Stay.
- This was sent from the Eyrie.

540
00:48:11.557 --> 00:48:13.224
(Door closes)

541
00:48:17.437 --> 00:48:19.689
What's she doing at the Eyrie?

542
00:48:19.815 --> 00:48:22.358
She hasn't been back there
since her wedding.

543
00:48:30.826 --> 00:48:32.702
(Ned) What news?

544
00:48:34.329 --> 00:48:36.789
(Catelyn) She's fled the capital.

545
00:48:39.126 --> 00:48:41.669
She says Jon Arryn was murdered.

546
00:48:41.795 --> 00:48:43.671
By the Lannisters.

547
00:48:43.797 --> 00:48:46.465
She says the king is in danger.

548
00:48:46.592 --> 00:48:48.843
She's fresh widowed. Cat.

549
00:48:48.969 --> 00:48:50.595
She doesn't know what she's saying.

550
00:48:50.721 --> 00:48:56.017
Lysa's head would be on a spike right now
if the wrong people had found that letter.

551
00:48:56.143 --> 00:48:58.311
Do you think she would risk her life.

552
00:48:58.437 --> 00:49:00.021
her son's life.

553
00:49:00.147 --> 00:49:03.524
if she wasn't certain
her husband was murdered?

554
00:49:10.741 --> 00:49:12.617
If this news is true...

555
00:49:12.743 --> 00:49:16.287
and the Lannisters conspire
against the throne.

556
00:49:16.413 --> 00:49:18.831
who but you can protect the king?

557
00:49:18.957 --> 00:49:21.208
They murdered the last Hand.

558
00:49:21.335 --> 00:49:23.544
Now you want Ned to take the job?

559
00:49:23.670 --> 00:49:27.548
The king rode for a month
to ask for Lord Stark's help.

560
00:49:27.674 --> 00:49:30.176
He's the only one he trusts.

561
00:49:31.678 --> 00:49:34.513
You swore the king an oath. my lord.

562
00:49:34.640 --> 00:49:38.225
He's spent half his life
fighting Robert's wars.

563
00:49:38.352 --> 00:49:40.353
He owes him nothing.

564
00:49:42.272 --> 00:49:45.483
Your father and brother
rode south once

565
00:49:45.609 --> 00:49:48.235
on a king's demand.

566
00:49:50.155 --> 00:49:52.281
A different time.

567
00:49:53.659 --> 00:49:55.743
A different king.

568
00:49:59.289 --> 00:50:01.290
- (Noisy chatter)
- (Drumming)

569
00:50:22.562 --> 00:50:24.522
(Hissing)

570
00:50:29.736 --> 00:50:31.737
(Gasps)

571
00:50:56.930 --> 00:51:00.433
When do I meet with the khal?
We need to begin planning the invasion.

572
00:51:00.559 --> 00:51:03.978
If Khal Drogo has promised you a crown.
you shall have it.

573
00:51:04.104 --> 00:51:07.148
- When?
- When their omens favor war.

574
00:51:08.275 --> 00:51:10.818
I piss on Dothraki omens.

575
00:51:10.944 --> 00:51:13.612
I've waited 17 years to get my throne back.

576
00:51:22.956 --> 00:51:25.958
- (Crowd ululating)
- (Grunting)

577
00:51:40.474 --> 00:51:41.766
(Cheering)

578
00:51:51.401 --> 00:51:53.360
(Speaks Dothraki)

579
00:51:53.487 --> 00:51:54.945
(Blades clang)

580
00:52:04.498 --> 00:52:05.831
(Screams)

581
00:52:13.548 --> 00:52:18.511
A Dothraki wedding without at least
three deaths is considered a dull affair.

582
00:52:19.888 --> 00:52:22.181
(Laughing)

583
00:52:31.233 --> 00:52:35.152
(Speaks Dothraki)

584
00:52:40.867 --> 00:52:43.911
A small gift. for the new khaleesi.

585
00:52:44.871 --> 00:52:47.456
Songs and histories from the Seven Kingdoms.

586
00:52:49.125 --> 00:52:50.543
Thank you. ser.

587
00:52:52.254 --> 00:52:54.922
Are you from my country?

588
00:52:55.048 --> 00:52:57.091
Ser Jorah Mormont of Bear Island.

589
00:52:57.217 --> 00:52:59.927
I served your father for many years.

590
00:53:00.053 --> 00:53:03.013
Gods be good. I hope to
always serve the rightful king.

591
00:53:26.246 --> 00:53:28.914
Dragon's eggs. Daenerys.

592
00:53:29.040 --> 00:53:31.792
from the Shadow Lands beyond Asshai.

593
00:53:31.918 --> 00:53:34.837
The ages have turned them to stone.

594
00:53:34.963 --> 00:53:36.922
but they will always be beautiful.

595
00:53:39.175 --> 00:53:40.843
Thank you. Magister.

596
00:54:49.537 --> 00:54:51.580
She's beautiful.

597
00:54:55.835 --> 00:54:57.086
Ser Jorah. I...

598
00:54:57.212 --> 00:54:59.964
I don't know how to say "thank you"
in Dothraki.

599
00:55:00.090 --> 00:55:02.883
There is no word for "thank you"
in Dothraki.

600
00:55:24.072 --> 00:55:26.031
Make him happy.

601
00:55:38.545 --> 00:55:40.212
(Waves crashing)

602
00:56:25.425 --> 00:56:27.426
- No.
- (Sobs)

603
00:56:30.764 --> 00:56:32.598
Do you know the common tongue?

604
00:56:37.437 --> 00:56:39.146
- (Pin clanks)
- No.

605
00:56:43.401 --> 00:56:45.611
Is "no" the only word that you know?

606
00:56:47.113 --> 00:56:48.447
No.

607
00:56:54.079 --> 00:56:56.163
(Continues sobbing)

608
00:57:16.810 --> 00:57:18.852
Rough night. Imp?

609
00:57:18.978 --> 00:57:20.938
If I get through this without squirting

610
00:57:21.064 --> 00:57:23.941
from one end or the other.
it'll be a miracle.

611
00:57:24.067 --> 00:57:25.859
I didn't pick you for a hunter.

612
00:57:25.985 --> 00:57:29.071
The greatest in the land -
my spear never misses.

613
00:57:30.156 --> 00:57:32.116
It's not hunting if you pay for it.

614
00:57:41.167 --> 00:57:43.210
Are you as good with a spear
as you used to be?

615
00:57:43.336 --> 00:57:45.796
No. but I'm still better than you.

616
00:57:45.922 --> 00:57:47.714
(Laughs)

617
00:57:48.800 --> 00:57:50.425
I know what I'm putting you through.

618
00:57:50.552 --> 00:57:52.219
Thank you for saying yes.

619
00:57:54.347 --> 00:57:56.640
I only ask you because I need you.

620
00:57:57.851 --> 00:58:00.394
You're a loyal friend. You hear me?

621
00:58:01.479 --> 00:58:03.063
A loyal friend.

622
00:58:03.189 --> 00:58:04.857
The last one I've got.

623
00:58:06.609 --> 00:58:08.777
- I hope I'll serve you well.
- You will.

624
00:58:10.071 --> 00:58:13.282
And I'll make sure you don't look
so fucking grim all the time.

625
00:58:14.617 --> 00:58:16.869
Come on. boys.
let's go kill some boar!

626
00:58:27.088 --> 00:58:28.589
Come on. you.

627
00:58:43.646 --> 00:58:44.980
(Whines)

628
00:58:53.907 --> 00:58:55.490
(Grunts)

629
00:58:59.412 --> 00:59:01.246
(Barks softly)

630
00:59:07.754 --> 00:59:09.421
(Woman gasping)

631
00:59:13.676 --> 00:59:15.302
(Woman moaning)

632
00:59:25.438 --> 00:59:27.105
(Grunting. moaning)

633
00:59:43.373 --> 00:59:44.831
(Gasps)

634
00:59:44.958 --> 00:59:47.751
- Stop! Stop.
- (Gasps)

635
00:59:52.632 --> 00:59:54.883
Are you completely mad?

636
00:59:55.009 --> 00:59:57.511
- He saw us.
- It's all right. it's all right.

637
00:59:57.637 --> 00:59:59.680
- It's all right.
- He saw us!

638
00:59:59.806 --> 01:00:01.932
I heard you the first time.

639
01:00:03.142 --> 01:00:04.726
(Whimpers)

640
01:00:06.688 --> 01:00:08.355
Quite the little climber. aren't you?

641
01:00:09.649 --> 01:00:12.442
- How old are you. boy?
- Ten.

642
01:00:12.568 --> 01:00:14.152
Ten.

643
01:00:22.996 --> 01:00:25.330
- The things I do for love.
- (Gasps)

644
01:00:26.000 --> 01:00:29.106
